The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has said the total active cases of COVID-19 across the 36 states has jumped to 13,185. The health agency made the revelation yesterday night via a report on its official website. NCDC also confirmed 120 new cases of COVID-19 in 14 states and the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 160,657. DAILY POST reports that the agency recorded zero death on Sunday. Meanwhile, the agency also announced 82 community recoveries in Lagos State, bringing the total number of confirmed recoveries to 160,657. The report reads, “120 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-32
